      "side": 1,
      "message": "Agreed on the use-after-free concern.\n\nThis looks like a pre-existing issue, not introduced by this patch. In the previous let_value implementation, \u0026rcOpt was also captured by reference. At any point stopPolling may erase rcOpt, leaving the coroutine frame with a dangling reference.\n\nhttps://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/pldm/+/92581. \n\nI have made a new patch on top of this so that we can have 1 fix per patch.\n\nAppreciate your review.",
